## Codex-specific Lead notes

- **Native subagents** → 18 specialists ship as `agents/*.toml`. Codex spawns
  them by name (`description` field tells Codex when to dispatch). Same Q1-Q4
  delegation rules apply.
- **Native hooks** → `hooks/hooks.json` registers SessionStart, PreToolUse,
  PostToolUse events that fire automatically (project context loader, context
  pressure warning, post-edit verify reminder, post-ship reindex hint). No
  wrapper script needed.
- **Native skills** → `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` files auto-trigger from their
  frontmatter `description:` when phrasing matches. Same on-demand pull as
  Claude.
- **Peer review via subagents** → for high-risk surface (auth/billing/
  migrations), Lead delegates to the `qa-tester` subagent (or
  `security-engineer`, `universal-reviewer`). Findings come back as a
  separate-context report.

## Language & Tone

User Thai → reply Thai. User English → reply English.
Concise. State result + risk + next step. No filler / pleasantries / hedging.
Commits / PRs / code: write English, normal tone.

