## Anti-bloat — keep it simple

- This file (AGENTS.md) = always-on judgment guidance
- Skills = on-demand workflow (auto-pulled by Codex when description matches)
- Hooks = deterministic enforcement (`hooks/hooks.json`)
- Bloat = Codex ignores rules. Move infrequent guidance to skills, move
  enforcement to hooks.

## Code intelligence — auto + manual

**Auto-triggers** (via `hooks/hooks.json`):
- SessionStart → project context loader injects git activity + setup checklist
- PreToolUse Bash/apply_patch → context-pressure warning when transcript large
- PostToolUse apply_patch → verify reminder before claiming done
- PostToolUse Bash → reindex hint after big merges

**Manual** (Lead invokes):
- Before edit symbol → check callers via `rg` or GitNexus MCP if connected
- Before commit → run `git diff` + lint + typecheck
- Before re-deciding → search history (`git log --grep=...`) or MemPalace MCP
- After major decision → write a brief ADR in `decisions/` if project keeps one

## Session hygiene

- Restart Codex between unrelated tasks (no `/clear` equivalent)
- Use `codex resume` to pick up a previous session
- Use `codex fork` to branch from a checkpoint
- Long task spans sessions → summarize state in a working note before exiting

## Before ship — STOP

- Run S1-S5, T1-T6, Q1-Q4, F1-F5 gates
- For high-risk surface (auth/billing/migrations) → delegate to the
  `qa-tester` subagent (universal floor) and `security-engineer` /
  `universal-reviewer` as routing dictates

Reviewer roles:
- **`qa-tester`** — correctness, business logic, tests (universal floor)
- **`security-engineer`** — security audit on auth/billing/data paths
- **`universal-reviewer`** — code quality, DRY, architecture smell
- **External Claude qa-tester** (cross-CLI) — if Claude Code installed, invoke
  `claude --dangerously-skip-permissions -p "review this diff"` in a separate
  shell for adversarial second opinion

## Hard stops — STOP and ask user

- 50k+ tokens no convergence → summarize + ask
- File system disagrees with claim → trust file, re-verify
- Destructive cmd (`rm -rf` / `git reset --hard` / force push) → announce + try reversible first
- User's intent unclear after 1 clarification → ask, don't guess

## Search

| Need | Tool |
|------|------|
| Plain text / filename | `rg` |
| Symbol / caller / impact | GitNexus MCP if connected, else `rg` + Read |
| External docs / pricing / news | Codex web search (`--search` flag) |

## Verification (post-change evidence)

Every change → show evidence (test output / curl / log). Can't verify → state why + risk.
UI change → drive a browser tool yourself. NEVER ask user for screenshot.

## Code quality + anti-spaghetti

- Match existing style — don't refactor adjacent unbroken code
- One source of truth — search before adding new helper/schema/type
- Surgical — every changed line traces to user request
- Comments only for intent / non-obvious
- No new deps without clear win
- Same pattern in 3+ places → centralize

## Goal-driven

Vague → verifiable goal. "add validation" → write test for invalid input → make pass.
"Fix bug" → reproducing test → fix until pass. "Refactor X" → tests pass before AND after.
Multi-step → state plan as `[step] → verify: [check]` per row.

